    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI have keymap to open a terminal.\n\nIt is extremely annoying to have a new terminal everytime I use my keymap because then I have 20 different terminals and I can never find the terminal I search for when I need it.\n\nIt is useless to open any terminal because then I can open a terminal with a long running command (like node or gcc) and I cannot do anything with it\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nA way, anything, to know if a terminal buffer is running a command or not (I want to know if I'm inside bash/fish and its available for a command. Or if the terminal run something like sleep 100/node and so I cannot do anything with the terminal at all)",
